definition.value: A carboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of N-carbamoyl-L-alpha-amino acid.
Dianion of (1S,2R)-1-C-(indol-3-yl)glycerol 3-phosphate arising from deprotonation of both phosphate OH groups.
Procollagen 5-hydroxy-L-lysine protonated at the 6-amino group.
Conjugate base of 3,7-dideoxy-D-threo-hepto-2,6-diuolosonic acid.
Dication of N-(3-aminopropyl)-4-aminobutanal arising from protonation of both nitrogens.
Dianion of beta-D-fructofuranosyl alpha-D-mannopyranoside 6(F)-phosphate arising from deprotonation of both phosphate OH groups.
Dianion of 3,3'-biflaviolin arising from selective deprotonation of the OH groups at the 2- and 2'-positions.
Dianion of 3,8'-biflaviolin arising from selective deprotonation of the OH groups at the 2- and 2'-positions.
Conjugate base of taurohyocholic acid.
A bile acid anion that is the conjugate base of hyodeoxycholic acid.
A  bile acid anion that is the conjugate base of murideoxycholic acid.
A steroid sulfate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid and sulfate functions of glycochenodeoxycholic acid 7-sulfate.
Conjugate base of 2-oxo-1,2-dihydroquinoline-4-carboxylic acid.
Dianion of N-acetylphosphinothricin obtained by deprotonation of carboxylic acid and phosphinate functions.
Dianion of N-acetyl-D-hexosamine 1-phosphate arising from deprotonation of both phosphate OH groups.
Conjugate base of phosphinothricin arising from deprotonation of the phosphinate function.
The conjugate base of a 7-O-beta-D-glucosylflavonol compound.
Tricarboxylate anion of (2R)-homocitric acid.
Dianion of UDP-alpha-D-glucose arising from deprotonation of both free OH groups on the diphosphate moiety.
Conjugate acid of 1D-myo-inositol 2-amino-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranoside arising from protonation of the nitrogen.
Conjugate acid of 1D-myo-inositol 2-(L-cysteinylamino)-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranoside arising from protonation of the amino acid nitrogen.
The dianion resulting from the removal of two protons from the phosphate group of 2,5-diamino-6-(1-D-ribitylamino)pyrimidin-4(3H)-one 5'-phosphate.
Zwitterionic form 6-(alpha-D-glucosaminyl)-1D-myo-inositol 1,2-cyclic phosphate having an anionic phosphate group and a protonated nitrogen.
Dianion of 1D-myo-inositol 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranoside 3-phosphate arising from deptonation of both OH groups of the phosphate.
Octaanion of precorrin-1 arising from global deprotonation of the carboxy groups.
Hexaanion of cob(II)yrinic acid arising from global deprotonation of the carboxy groups.
Trianion of 2-carboxy-4-methyl-5-[(2-phosphonooxy)ethylidene]-2,5-dihydrothiazole arising from deprotonation of carboxylic acid and phosphate functions.
The conjugate base of a 2-hydroxy carboxylic acid.
An acyl-CoA(4-) that is the tetraanion of 1,4-dihydroxy-2-naphthoyl-CoA arising from deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate functions.
Dianion of 2-amino-4,5-dihydroxy-6-oxo-7-(phosphonooxy)heptanoic acid having anionic carboxyl and phosphate groups and a protonated amino group.
The carboxylate anion formed from an alpha-D-glucosiduronic acid
Trianion of UDP-N-acetyl-2-amino-2-deoxy-D-glucuronic acid arising from deprotonation of carboxylic acid and phosphate functions.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion resulting from the removal of a proton from both of the carboxy groups of 2-(E)-O-feruloyl-D-galactaric acid.
Zwitterionic form of beta-L-aspartylhydroxamic acid having an anionic carboxy group and a protonated amino group.
Any unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) in which the fatty acyl group contains a double bond at position 11.
Any Delta(12)-acyl-CoA in which the mono- and di-phosphate groups are fully deprotonated.
Conjugate base of S-sulfanylglutathione having both carboxy groups in anionic form and a protonated primary amino group.
An ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of sphingosylphosphocholine, obtained by protonation of the amino group. Major species at pH 7.3.
The dianion resulting from deprotonation of the phosphate group as well as removal of the acidic proton from the carbon adjacent to the 2-oxo group of precursor Z.
An  organophosphate oxoanion that is the dianion of L-galactose 1-phosphate arising from deprotonation of both OH groups of the phosphate.

An organophosphate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of 4-deoxy-4-formamido-alpha-L-arabinopyranosyl di-trans,poly-cis-undecaprenyl phosphate, arising from deprotonation of the free OH group of the phosphate.
Conjugate base of thyroxine sulfate having anionic carboxy and sulfate groups and the amino group protonated.
Anion of delphinidin 3-O-(6''-O-malonyl)-beta-D-glucoside arising from deprotonation of the malonyl carboxy and 5-hydroxy groups.
Dianion of ternatin C5 arising from deprotonation of the malonyl carboxy and 5-and 7- hydroxy groups.
Anion of delphinidin delphinidin 3-O-(6''-O-malonyl)-beta-D-glucoside-3'-O-beta-D-glucoside arising from deprotonation of the malonyl carboxy and 5-hydroxy groups.
Trianion of all-trans-polyprenyl diphosphate arising from deprotonation of the three OH groups of the diphosphate.
Tricarboxylate anion of of (2E)-but-2-ene-1,2,3-tricarboxylic acid.
Conjugate acid of (R)-piperazine-2-carboxamide arising from selective protonation at the 4-position.
